# From + price formatting

When **"From" prefixes a price** (e.g. `From £150` in a treatment row, extras grid, or price column), **do not** put plain text like `From £150` in one span at a single size.

## Required pattern

- **"From":** `text-sm font-normal`
- **Amount:** `text-lg sm:text-xl font-bold tabular-nums` (include `&pound;` or currency in this span)
- **Pair:** wrap in `inline-flex items-baseline gap-1.5` so the gap between "From" and the figure is always the same.

```html
<span class="inline-flex items-baseline gap-1.5 font-sans text-gray-900 tabular-nums">
  <span class="text-sm font-normal">From</span>
  <span class="text-lg sm:text-xl font-bold tabular-nums">&pound;150</span>
</span>
```

## Alignment in a row (title left, price right)

If the row uses `flex justify-between` with variable-width left copy, give the price block a **fixed width** and **right-align** the pair so every row lines up (see Injectables Fat Dissolve):

```html
<div class="shrink-0 w-44 flex justify-end">
  <span class="inline-flex items-baseline gap-1.5 font-sans text-gray-900">
    <span class="text-sm font-normal">From</span>
    <span class="text-lg sm:text-xl font-bold tabular-nums">&pound;180</span>
  </span>
</div>
```

## When this does **not** apply

- Normal prose ("from simple to bold") — no special formatting.
- Prices **without** a "From" prefix — use the same treatment-title + price pattern as Facials (`text-lg sm:text-xl` on both title and price, semibold title).

## Examples in repo

`nails.astro` (Extras + Nail Art), `injectables.astro` (Fat Dissolve).
